I honestly didn’t know what to expect with these snacks... since mostly ‘bugak’ are eaten as either side dish banchans or just as snack. They’re normally coated with sticky sweet rice so it’s a balance of sweet and salty. The pumpkin bugak was pretty good. Not too sticky on the teeth. Super crispy and crunchy. You could definitely taste the pumpkin. The laver bugak was pretty sweet and salty. Super sticky on the teeth. Nonetheless, I liked it a lot. The hot chili bugak was a little too spicy for me but my mom seemingly enjoyed it!#Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08L

Gim Bugak .Gim means seaweed in Korean, and is quite possibly the most used ingredient in the restaurant. It's pronounced like kim and can be used in so many different ways. Seaweed is brushed with the "bugak glue" or rice paste and dried over night then fried for 15 seconds. It puffs like a chicharron and is insanely crunchy. We fry them in the morning before service, after it dries, we break it into small squares  making it the ultimate snack. It's the amuse-bouche at @atoboynyc and the kids that come into eat always ask for seconds. I'm trying to convince  chef @jparkato to sell them at @wholefoods but he just chuckles. .....#food #gim #seaweed #bugak #korean #fry #nyc #newyork #atoboy #ny #manhattan #nomad #insta #instagram #eeeeeats #crunchy #snacks #thebest #bomb #atoboy

*I received discounted product in exchange for my review* 🥠HOW TO USE: open and enjoy! Has a resealable top to keep food fresh 🥠PROS: - Bugak is a kind of traditional Korean snack made under the Yung Ju, Soback Mountain in S. Korea- almost all ingredients are cultivated in the above mountain- no food additives, no artificial flavors - comes in six flavors: Pumkin, Laver, Hot Pepper, Carrot, Burdock and Potato- made to enhance the flavor of the raw materials - contains raw sugar cane and boiled salicomia herbácea salt- low price point (retails for $8.99/3 pack of 1.23oz in each bag or about 50 pieces. Can also be purchased individually for $3.99/bag) 🥠CONS:- hot pepper flavor is very hot! - Laver flavor is seaweed so some people may not enjoy that taste- Pumkin/Laver/Hot Pepper appear to be the only ones you can buy in a 3-pack (which is a better deal) 🥠OVERALL, I tried Pumkin, Laver and Hot Pepper. They taste very much like potato chips! I enjoyed the Pumkin the best, the Laver was ok but the Hot Pepper was way too hot for me. But I think they have a lot more Pros to them and they are a unique crispy chip that is fun to eat! I would love to try the other flavors and would like to see more variety in the 3-pack because that price is a better deal. Thanks to HanBuGak for allowing me to sample.#Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08L #ad #Sponsored

#첫줄..2019 MICHELIN Guide Seoul_One Star한식공간(Hansikgonggan)Lunch Course(1): 부각(Bugak, Vegetable and Seaweed Chips)..For a taste of the Korean past meets the present, head over to Hansikgonggan, a Korean restaurant helmed by Chef Cho Hee-suk and co-run by Chef Jeong Gyeong-il. Hailed as the godmother of Korean cuisine, Cho is committed to passing on her knowledge - based on years of experience and research – to the younger generation of chefs, while interpreting the traditional flavors with contemporary sensibilities for the modern diner. Expect both the expected and the unexpected, with a good dose of love and finesse...완연한 가을 날, 나무가 주는 안정감과 동시에 유리밖으로 시원하게 펼쳐지는 창덕궁의 풍경을 바라보며 즐기는 고즈넉한 한 끼를 제공 받을 수 있는 한식 다이닝 '한식공간'을 찾았어요. 오랜만에 조희숙 셰프님을 뵈었어요. 셰프님이 너무 반가웁게 맞이해주셔서 얼마나 기뻤는지 몰라요. 더군다나 이번에 미슐랭 원스타를 받으셨잖아요. 마치 제가 받은거마냥 좋아했네요. 축하드립니다...오늘은 한식공간에서 점심코스를 먹었어요. 언젠가는 한식의 멋과 맛을 한껏 즐길수 있는 이곳에서 식사하고 싶었는데 말이죠. 꿈이 이루진것이죠...첫번째 메뉴는 '부각 바구니'였어요. 부각은 찹쌀 풀을 발라서 말려두었다가 필요할 때 기름에 튀겨먹는 음식이죠. 겨울철 저장 식품으로 풋고추, 김, 깻잎, 두릅, 감자, 다시마, 우엉 등 종류가 다양하답니다. 한식공간에서는 김, 깻잎, 돼지감자 그리고 들깨송이 부각이 다왔어요. 들깨송이 부각 짱이죠...부각(Bugak, Vegetable and Seaweed Chips): This refers to a variety of deep-fried vegetables coated with glutinous rice paste and dried for preservation. A food that is prepared for winter, bugak can be made with many different vegetables, including green pepper, seaweed, perilla leaves, fatsia shoots, kelp, and burdock leaves, among others...#조희숙 #한식공간 #한식 #한국음식 #음식 #전통 #foods #cuisine #koreancuisine #hansikgonggan #lunch #lunchcourse #coursemenu #michelinrestaurant #koreanrestaurant #restaurant #onestar #bugak #seaweed #potato #deepfried #干炸片 #乾炸片

REVIEW: Korean Snacks Pumpkin, Laver & Hot Pepper BugakThis is my first time to review Korean Snacks. I was so excited to try them all together with my husband.My favorite is Pumpkin Snack, reminds me of baked sweet potato chips. It is sweet and crunchy I really like. The next one I tried was Laver Snack, it reminds me of chicharones but it has seaweed on it. It has a seaweed/seafood taste to it and somewhat bland as well.My husband's favorite is the Hot Pepper Snacks, he really likes spicy food. The chili used is different from Jalapeno pepper which he find interesting. Explained to him that in Asia we have different varietr of chilis. Overall, we really enjoyed the snacks and it is something new to try on. Thanks at 0.8L for the opportunity to review this product.#Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08L

Sahabat, sudah tahu kisah Wakaf Habib Bugak yang hasilnya masih dirasakan sampai sekarang?.Awal mula cerita terjadi pada tahun 1800-an. Habib Bugak yang saat itu masih berada di Aceh, sudah memiliki gagasan untuk mengumpulkan uang, guna membeli tanah di Makkah untuk diwakafkan kepada jamaah calon haji..Selain dari dana yang dimilikinya sendiri, Habib Bugak menjadi inisiator pengumpulan dana dari masyarakat Aceh..Ketika Habib Bugak berangkat ke Tanah Suci, dia membawa bekal dana untuk wakaf. Dan begitu sampai, niatan wakaf itu direalisasikannya. Dia membeli tanah yang lokasinya kala itu persis di samping Masjidil Haram..Di atas tanah itu didirikan penginapan untuk menampung jamaah calon haji asal Aceh. Jamaah pun tak lagi bingung mencari tempat tinggal selama berada di Makkah..Lalu saat Masjidil Haram direnovasi, tanah wakaf ini termasuk digunakan untuk perluasan lintasan thawaf. Oleh nadzir (pengelola) wakaf, uang ganti rugi digunakan membeli dua bidang tanah di kawasan yang berjarak 500-an meter dari Masjidil Haram..Tanah itu dibangun hotel oleh pengusaha dengan sistem bagi hasil. Dari situ lah, bonus untuk jamaah Aceh mengalir tiap musim haji. Seperti pada tahun ini, lebih dari Rp 20 miliar dibagikan kepada seluruh jamaah asal Aceh..Masya Allah, Barakallah Sahabat. 😇Follow @wakafdt untuk mengetahui inspirasi wakaf lainnya. www.wakafdt.org...#wakafdt #belajarwakaf #dirumahaja #aagym #dt #muda #daaruttauhiid #bugakasyi #hajibugakasyi #aceh #asyi #bugak

Hansik Goo(d)! 🇰🇷 Whilst casual Korean diners can be found in pretty much every corner of Hong Kong, we are far from being spoiled for choice if we want a refined Korean dining experience. In comes Hansik Goo, which bravely opened during this weird period in life - and it’s clear that they had nothing to fear, given the strength of the food offered here! There aren’t any theatrics, no ‘prized’ ingredients, nothing fancy - just careful observation of authentic flavours with refined and technical execution. Yukhoe was prepared fairly traditionally, with only just the right amount of seasoning to allow the subtle flavours of the meat shine through. In addition to the common pairing with pear, artichoke chips were served on the side for texture and slight nuttiness. Bibim guksu saw strands of silky soft noodles (believe buckwheat was used rather than the more traditional somen) coated in a balanced sauce with just the right amount of kick, served alongside impossibly tender barbecued slices of pork. The crunchiness and sweetness of the ‘young’ kimchi rounded off the entire course and also contrasted with the funkiness of the two-year kimchi served previously. My favourite dish of the meal was the most avant-garde one, the samgyetang risotto - not for its innovative use of risotto outside of the chicken rather than sticky rice used as stuffing inside the chicken, but for the tweaks and changes made to the otherwise traditional samgyetang soup. Ginseng and chicken shone through clearly, with each being a distinct element that worked well together. Thickened slightly (rather than being left as a traditional broth) for compatibility with the risotto, I wouldn’t mind having bowlfuls of this, particularly on a rainy day. All in all, a precise exercise of Korean flavours!————7-course tasting menu (around $800 per head)📍Hansik Goo🇭🇰 8 Lyndhurst Terrace, Central————#dflCentral #dflHK

Thank you to @0.8Lusa for allowing me to try the product for $3.99 in exchange for an honest review. .I am a foodie at  heart ❤️. First, was impressed that I received three full size bags of Korean Traditional Pumpkin +Laver, Hot Pepper Bugak (hot pepper okra) & Lavar Bugak (seaweed in rice paper). .My favorite was Lavar Bugak, Pumpkin and then theHot Pepper Bugak. The seeweed had a sweet sour taste and once very crunchy. I am not big fan of pumpkin, but still enjoyed because the chip was sweet. The hot Pepper was my least favorite. Oh, I love okra, but not as a chip and it was a bit spicy for me. However, the spicy might work for someone else..In my opinion a healthy product and I definitely would buy and recommend to others. I can see that a vegan and vegetarian would like. 김부각 Korean Traditional BugakSeaweed Laver, Pumpkin and Hot Pepper flavor Bugak is a deep-fried vegetables coated with glutinous rice paste. The ingredients being fried include laver, perilla leaves, chili pepper, and many other. It is eaten as a sidedish with rice.It does not include food additives and artificial flavors.I love trying new snack from Korea. That is the thing with me. I like everything about South Korea and exploring it more gives me that amazing feeling of knowing another country culture.  Whenever I travel I will go to Asian store and try new thing, just one or two but that is often enough to learn something. Korean snacks are amazing and often you can find something even healthy there. I tried that crispy snack (all three packages! in one sitting) on one evening and I love it. Enough crispy, rich in flavor but not overly salty or sweet. Just that burst of flavor enough to feel you when you are in need. 浮刻. 부각을 일군다.예부터 어르신들은 부각은 ＇튀긴다＇고 말하지않고 ＇일군다’라고 한다고 합니다.다른 튀김과는 달리 부각은 그냥 튀김옷에 담갔다가 꺼내면 되는 것이 아니라 붓으로 찹쌀을 하나하나 바른 다음 그것을 또 말리는 과정이 필요해서 대단히 손이 많이 가는 편입니다.거기다 말리는 데 시간이 들다 보니 날씨를 잘못 고르면 기도 전에 재료가 상해 버리는 경우가 생기기도 왕왕 했다고 합니다 한다.튀기는 것에 비행 요령이 많이 필요한데다 드는 품에 비해 먹는 간 또 한순간이다 보니.종가집 며느리들에게는 거의 저주와 같은 존재로 전해져왔다고 합니다 ..1Year .우연한 인연으로 만난 김총각네 .형제들만의 힘으로 수년간 소중히 키워온 브랜드를함께 새롭게 해보자고 이야기 한지가 벌써 1년이네요.브랜드는 함께 고민하고 함께 키워가는 것이고 브랜드의 정체성은 우리가 아닌 만든 사람의 일상과 생각 그리고 제품 그 자체에 있는 것을 함께 도와 끌어내는 것이라고 생각합니다.그러한 관점에서 2인3각으로 함께 조심스레 브랜드를 만들어 왔기에 그 어떤 프로젝트보다 애정이 깊은 김총각네.남원의 햇살아래 김총각네의 이 사진 한 장 만으로도 따스하고 푸근한 가을을 느껴집니다..드디어 추석시즌 리뉴얼 완료~.#Bugak #crispy #chips #traditional #branding #local #부각 #김총각네 #남원 #전통식품 #지역농산물 #브랜딩 #브랜드컨설팅 #insighttrip #filamentandcompany

.[Madame Jade] Chilli Pepper BugakBugak (부각) is a variety of vegetarian twigim (deep-fried dish) in Korean cuisine. It is made by deep frying dried vegetables or seaweed coated with chapssal-pul (찹쌀풀; glutinous rice paste) and then drying them again.  It goes great with rice or/and alcoholic beverages.Bugak is a relatively rare culinary technique in Korean cuisine and often associated with Korean temple cuisine.Madam Jade’s bugak is made by following the traditional procedures so that it would not go soggy easy, keeping crunchiness and still not oily.Enjoy this as side dish or healthy snack.부각은 말린 해초나 야채 등에 찹쌀풀을 묻힌 뒤 말려서 기름에 튀긴 전통 음식 입니다. 마담제이드의 고추부각은 시간이 지나도 눅눅해지지 않고, 기름지지 않으면서도 바삭한 식감이 되도록 여러차례 손이가는 정성을 들여 만들었습니다.건강한 간식이나 고소한 반찬으로 맛있게 즐겨보세요..#정성가득고추부각#전통음식#마담제이드 #madamejade#vegetarianfood #vegetatian #newmenu#chillipepperbugak#bugak#koreanfood#boramykitchen

Sahabat, sudah tahu kisah Wakaf Habib Bugak yang hasilnya masih dirasakan sampai sekarang?.Awal mula cerita terjadi pada tahun 1800-an. Habib Bugak yang saat itu masih berada di Aceh, sudah memiliki gagasan untuk mengumpulkan uang, guna membeli tanah di Makkah untuk diwakafkan kepada jamaah calon haji..Selain dari dana yang dimilikinya sendiri, Habib Bugak menjadi inisiator pengumpulan dana dari masyarakat Aceh..Ketika Habib Bugak berangkat ke Tanah Suci, dia membawa bekal dana untuk wakaf. Dan begitu sampai, niatan wakaf itu direalisasikannya. Dia membeli tanah yang lokasinya kala itu persis di samping Masjidil Haram..Di atas tanah itu didirikan penginapan untuk menampung jamaah calon haji asal Aceh. Jamaah pun tak lagi bingung mencari tempat tinggal selama berada di Makkah..Lalu saat Masjidil Haram direnovasi, tanah wakaf ini termasuk digunakan untuk perluasan lintasan thawaf. Oleh nadzir (pengelola) wakaf, uang ganti rugi digunakan membeli dua bidang tanah di kawasan yang berjarak 500-an meter dari Masjidil Haram..Tanah itu dibangun hotel oleh pengusaha dengan sistem bagi hasil. Dari situ lah, bonus untuk jamaah Aceh mengalir tiap musim haji. Seperti pada tahun ini, lebih dari Rp 20 miliar dibagikan kepada seluruh jamaah asal Aceh..www.wakafdt.org...#wakafdt #belajarwakaf #dirumahaja #aagym #dt #muda #daaruttauhiid #bugakasyi #hajibugakasyi #aceh #asyi #bugak

I’ve never tried “Bugak” @hanbugak before , so I was actually curious of how this snack would taste. Bugak is a Korean traditional snack made by deep frying dried vegetables or seaweed then coated with glutinous rice paste and then drying them again. This snack did not disappoint, love the crunchiness and it’s sweet and salty flavor. I got 3 different varieties , the Laver (seaweed), Pumpkin and Hot Pepper. They’re all good but Hot Pepper 🌶 was my favorite. It can be enjoyed on its own or eaten as #banchan (accompaniment to cooked rice) or #anju (accompaniment to alcoholic beverages). Bugak is a very interesting snack and I really enjoyed it and will definitely buy again! Got these snacks at a discounted price from @0.8l_usa for testing purposes. #Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumpkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08l

I love trying out new foods so when I saw the Korean Traditional Bugak available to review for $3.99 I bought it. Bugak is made by deep frying vegetables coated with glutinous rice paste. It’s a great vegetarian snack and really tasty. I tried three flavors this time.Pumpkin: This flavor was really good and tasted pretty similar to a potato chip. I think the Pumpkin flavor would be good for anyone who likes chips.Lavar: This is the seaweed flavor and is made with seaweed paper. I really loved this flavor as I love to snack on seaweed often and this is better than the usual seaweed snacks I usually buy.Green Hot Pepper: This flavor was super hot! I usually like hot pepper and I did like the flavor but it is really hot. Overall I am really glad I got to try out the Bugak. This was new to me and I loved it! This was a great healthy vegetarian snack!#Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08L

🌟 Best Night View Spots in Seoul 🌟1.Bugak SkywayBugak skyway is a 19km long road that runs from the northeast side of Bugaksan Mountain. It is one of Seoul’s most scenic routes and a perfect spot to see the city at night. On the route the beautiful Palgakjeong pavilion is also located.2.Namsan TowerNamsan Tower is a perfect spot to see the Seoul night view. It is easy to access and is located in the middle of the city. The view is amazing both from the observatory deck and the top of the tower. 3.Seoul Sky (Lotte Tower)Lotte Tower opened in 2017 so it is a newer popular spot to see Seoul at night. The observatory ‘Seoul Sky’ is located 555 m above ground and will make you feel like you are walking amongst the clouds. Price: 27.000 won (adult), 24.000 won (children)4.63 BuildingThe 63 building is located on Yeouido island and is one of the most well-known symbols of Seoul. There is an observatory deck located at the top of the building where you can see the beautiful view of the Han River at night. Price: 13.000 won (adult), 11.000 won (children)5.Banpo BridgeBanpo Bridge is famous for its colorful waterfall show that runs at 8 pm, 8:30 pm and 9 pm for 20 minutes. Enjoy the show while having a bite to eat from the many street food carts that are there. #seoul #nightview #korea #night #skyway #bugak #namsantower #lottetower #seoulsky #63building #banpobridge #watershow #travel #traveltips #triends

Not Skincare, but #TextureTuesday with FOOD! ⁣⁣Korean Han Bugak (courtesy of @0.8L_USA)  Bugak describes a Korean traditional snack and I received 3 bags of these crispy treats: 🎃Pumpkin, 🌊Laver (seaweed) and 🌶Hot Chili Pepper.  These are made in Yeongju, Sobaek Mountain, South Korea and almost all of the ingredients are harvested from this clean region. These snacks do not contain any artificial flavors or food additives and rely on the veggies + pure raw cane sugar and salicornia herbacea salt, which is a salt that contains salicornia, a marshland plant that contains iron, calcium, taurine and other rich minerals. ⁣⁣Tasting Time!! The first one I tried was the hot pepper ~ this is SO good.  It is a little bit spicy, because some of the pepper pieces still have the seeds, which are the hottest part of the pepper.  I don't know if these are baked or fried, but they are so crispy but very light and the coating of sugar + salt helps balance the bitterness of the pepper.⁣⁣Next up ~ pumpkin!! These are more like chips and don't melt in your mouth like the pepper ~ but they have a great crunch to them.  This one was more sweet with a touch of salt.  Of course, I ate this bag in one sitting!! hahaha⁣⁣Last was the Laver.  Now, I have had seaweed crunches before, and I do love them. However, this one really had the taste of the ocean with it & I found it to be overpowering in a bad way.  I didn't eat these by themselves ~ instead, I crushed them up and sprinkled them on dishes to help cut down on the seaweedy taste.  They were ALMOST there, but it's like they weren't rinsed enough.⁣⁣I really loved the Hot Pepper & Pumpkin flavors and I noticed they have others, like potato, carrot & burdock.. I would love to try them all! ⁣⁣#prsample #unboxingbeauty_kfood #foodporn #pumpkin #koreansnacks #snacks #crispysnack #Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08L #review #foodreview #kfood #koreanfoodsnacks

TWIGIM: deep fried... 😍 Quail from France brined with cheongjang, yondu, mirin, soju, garlic, jalapeño, salt, sugar, and deep fried with sweet rice flour paste + spruce honey glaze + spruce salt + eung-i...“There is a uniquely Korean way of frying called BUGAK. Habib Bugak Al-Asyi, yang bernama lengkap Habib Abdurrahman Bin Alwi Al-Habsyi. Ialah sosok darmawan yang telah mewakafkan tanahnya untuk dimanfaatkan warga Aceh yang pergi berhaji atau menempuh pendidikan di tanah suci.Habib Bugak asal Aceh yang datang ke Makkah tahun 1223 hijriah itu membeli tanah sekitar daerah Qusyasyiah yang sekarang berada di sekitar Bab Al Fath (antara Marwah dan Mesjid Haram). Saat itu, masa Kerajaan Ustmaniah.Namun, kemudian, pemerintah Arab Saudi pada masa Raja Malik Sa'ud bin Abdul Azis, melakukan pengembangan Masjidil Haram. Tanah wakaf Habib Bugak untuk masyarakat Aceh terkena proyek tersebut. Rumah Habib Bugak digusur dengan pemberian ganti rugi.Badan pengelola tanah wakaf itu kemudian menggunakan uang tersebut untuk membeli dua lokasi lahan yakni di daerah Ajyad sekitar, 500 dan 700 meter dari Masjidil Haram. Kedua tanah ini kemudian menjadi aset wakaf.Lahan pertama dengan jarak 500 meter dari Masjidil Haram dibangun hotel bintang lima dengan kamar sekitar 350-an unit. Di lahan kedua dengan jarak 700 meter dari Haram, dibangun hotel bintang lima dengan kamar sekitar 1.000 unit.Dari keuntungan lainnya, Nazhir membeli dua areal lahan seluas 1.600 meter persegi dan 850 meter persegi di Kawasan Aziziah. Tahun 2009 di kedua lahan ini dibangun pemondokan khusus untuk jamaah asal Embarkasi Aceh.Hasil keuntungan pengelolaan hata wakaf inilah yang sejak tahun 2006 dibagikan ke jamaah haji asal Aceh. Pada tahun 2008, Pemerintah Aceh menerima Rp14,54 miliar dari Baitul Asyi sebagai uang pengganti sewa rumah bagi 3.635 jamaah haji asal Aceh. Per jamaah mendapat sekitar Rp4 juta-an.Sumber : Lintas AtjehVidio By : @tgkmuda ...Follow @update.aceh Hastag #updateaceh #habib #bugak #matang #aceh #indonesia #pecintarasulullah #pewarisnabi #cucunabi #habaib #ulama #ulamaaceh #ulamajawa #ulamaaswaja

일전에 피드에 올렸던 김부각 만든거, 튀겨먹었어요.새우깡 맛과 향이 찐하게 나면서 바사삭 하고 부서지는 식감, 김의 향과 기름에 튀긴 고소함이 어우러져서 정말 강추합니다. 장마철되면 실온에 보관중인 김들, 붉으스름 변색되며 눅어지고 맛이 떨어지는데 이때 찹쌀풀쒀서 김에 발라 토핑으로 마른새우나 깨, 슬라이스아몬드 등 올려보세요. 스낵으로 최곱니다.백화점이나 마트에서 완제 김부각 팔지만 이만큼 맛있기 힘들고 뭣보다 비싸서 맘껏 먹기 어렵잖아요.만들기 어렵지 않구요, 궁금하시면 제 유튭 영상 올렸으니 참조하셔도 좋습니다.여름되면 수박 많이 드시지요. 저는 대놓고 수박껍데기 예찬론자입니다. 요맘때 나오는 박( 흥부네 지붕의 그 박)으로 나물 볶거나 국 끓이면 하얗고 매끈 쫄깃한 것이 시원~ 하여 고급진 맛인데, 호박처럼 아무데서나 팔지않아 먹을 타이밍을 놓치곤 하거든요. 그럴땐 아쉬운대로 수박사서 빨간 속 퍼내고, 초록 겉껍질 필로로 벗긴후 하얀 부분을 소금에 절였다 꼭 짜서 노각무치듯이 무쳐보세요. 오이무침보다, 노각무침보다, 박나물 비슷한데 더 오돌오돌, 아닥아닥 맛나답니다. 음식물 쓰레기로 나갈게 별로 없고, 별미인 수박나물무침, 보리밥에 올려 비벼드셔도 좋고, 비빔국수에 올려도 좋고, 죽이나 누룽밥 먹을때 함께 먹으면 입맛 깨분~~ 하지요. 까무잡잡한건 수박장아찌 건져 참기름 한방울 떨군겁니다.이것도 영상 찍었으니 담주쯤 올려보겠습니다. #수제김부각#새우김부각#지리멸부각#간식#반찬#안주#맥주안주#심폐소생김부각#수박껍질무침#수박껍질장아찌#비빔국수#강식당비빔국수양념 사용한, 니가 비비바락국수 #매운국수#집밥#홈쿡#kfood#snack#banchan#bugak#delicious#driedshrimps bugak, #driedanchovy  bugak #pickledwatermelonrind #seasonedwatermelonrind#spicynoodle#healthy#simplerecipes #koreangrandmastyle

Hanbugak has several snacks that healthy and delicious. I'm reviewing the laver, red pepper and pumpkin snacks. These snacks are from South Korea. They make this in a clean area under the Yung ja, Soback mountain. Almost all the ingredient are cultivated there, and doesn't contain food additives and artificial flavors. They made this with the main ingredient either laver, pumpkin, red peppers. Following with how they cover all the main ingredient in is glutinous rice, corn oil, raw sugar and boiled salicomia herbacea salt. Each snack taste different but very tasty. The laver one, taste spicy, savory and slightly sweet. This one is a heated treat that can burn the mouth but was very addicting to eat while watching Netflix. The pepper was crunchy and didn't stick to my teeth. The pumpkin one was sweet and slightly hard. You can hear the crunch. This pairs well with the pepper to get rid of the spiciness. The laver one which is seaweed had more of a savory and salty taste. It almost tasted like roasted seaweed. It was very tasty. The laver one did stick to my teeth a little bit. I do think this snacks are great and healthy choice to snack. I give this a 10/10.#Koreanfood #vegetarian #koreansnack #bugak #HanBuGak #Pumkin #HotPepper #Laver #healthysnack #vegan #08liter #08L

Perilla bugak. .Perilla is a plant found mostly in Asia, and used more than most in Korean cuisine. It's part of the mint family and at #atoboy it's a very key component in many of our dishes. In this method we brush it with a rice paste known in Korean as chapssal-pal. It's brushed on both sides of the leaf and dried over night. We individually fry each leaf at a very low temperature and lay them on paper towels. After, we dehydrate them for atleast two days, till you get a sweet crispy perilla bugak, our garnish for our steak dish at @atoboynyc .....#food #foodporn #nyc #learnsomething #americancookingkorean #inspiration #keeppushing #cooking #truecooks #insta #instagram #perilla #korean #bugak #dehydrationstation

Bugak (Korean chips) - seaweed, fish skin, chilli, perilla leaf .We all know the purpose of kimchi is to preserve vegetables for winter. But not many of us know that they also preserve vegetables by deep-frying it and drying it out. This is called Bugak. Traditionally it is a korean temple food, and is vegetarian as Buddhism heavily influenced Korean cuisine since it was introduced to the country in 372 (Former Qin Era). But Hangsik Goo is no tradition. The modern restaurant gives the ancient recipe a new twist, deep-frying fish skin as well! Vegetarians might need to take a second look at the menu. Read the tiny words!.#Bugak #Korean #Templefood #Vegetarian #Tradition #HansikGoo #Central #foodnote101
